{
  "message": "fuzz(detect-filesystem): 20 structured seeds across SeedImage \u00d7 magic\ncombinations \u00d7 mutation paths\n\nfuzz_detect_filesystem drives ffs_core::detect_filesystem +\nFrankenFsEngine::{inspect_image,parse_ext4,parse_btrfs} against six\nSeedImage shapes (Ext4Clean / Ext4Dirty / BtrfsClean / Zeroes / Raw /\nTruncated) and asserts (a) classification is deterministic for the\nsame input, (b) inspect_image and parse_* agree on the carried\nsuperblock when ext4/btrfs is detected. Existing 5 ad-hoc seeds\ncovered only one default per shape.\n\nAdds 20 seeds spanning every documented branch:\n\n  Default-shape seeds:\n  * Ext4Clean default, Ext4Dirty default\n  * BtrfsClean with stamp toggle (re-stamp tree block vs trust the\n    harness's pre-stamped checksum)\n  * Zeroes (1024 bytes of 0x00)\n\n  Raw-bytes (Raw mode) shapes:\n  * ext4 magic at sb+0x38 only (otherwise zero)\n  * btrfs magic at BTRFS_SUPER_INFO_OFFSET+0x40 only\n  * 256 bytes of 0xFF garbage (no magic anywhere)\n  * both magics simultaneously (drives the precedence path)\n  * ext4 magic + invalid block_size_log (parse rejects after detect)\n  * raw 16 bytes (well below superblock \u2014 must reject)\n\n  Truncated mode (Ext4Clean image then truncate):\n  * truncate to 0\n  * truncate to 256 (below sb offset)\n  * truncate to 1024 (exactly at sb offset, no sb content)\n\n  Targeted mutate_bytes against the 7-entry EXT4_INTERESTING table:\n  * magic flipped (offset 3 = sb+0x38, mutate_byte)\n  * state byte cleared (offset 4 = sb+0x3A, write_u16_le 0)\n  * block_size_log corrupted with u32::MAX (offset 2)\n  * 3-mutation pass corrupting sb start, magic, and state\n\n  Targeted mutate_bytes against the 10-entry BTRFS_INTERESTING table:\n  * magic flipped (offset 1 = sb+0x40)\n  * csum_type bogus (offset 7 = sb+0xC4, write_u16_le 0x7FFF)\n\nValidated by an 11 s libFuzzer run: 231k executions over the new\ncorpus, no crashes.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
